
[1]ejectment

   EJECT'MENT, n. Literally, a casting out; a dispossession.

   1. In law, a writ or action which lies for the recovery of possession
   of land from which the owner has been ejected, and for trial of title.
   Ejectment may be brought by the lessor against the lessee for rent in
   arrear, or for holding over his term; also by the lessee for years, who
   has been ejected before the expiration of his term.
